sec.p:
To compare the efficacy of the rainbow and standard mechanisms, we determined the fluence of the single laser pulse that provided the same lifetime of the PNB around a mono-NP cluster as was achieved for the rainbow PNB. The PNB lifetimes close to those of the rainbow PNBs required the following fluences of the single 532 nm laser pulse:
for NSP cluster - 3-4 fold (48 mJ/cm2 vs. 14 mJ/cm2 in rainbow mode);
for NS cluster - 2-3 fold (27 mJ/cm2 vs. 10 mJ/cm2 in rainbow mode).
